1 provisions of the Kansas public employees retirement system act of 2009
2 shall be not less than the benefit that the teacher was entitled to under the
3 Kansas public employees retirement system act of 2015 at the time of the
4 transfer. Participating employers under K.S.A. 74-4931, and amendments
5 thereto, shall be subject to all obligations under the Kansas public
6 employees retirement system act of 2009 for the teachers being transferred
7 under this section.
8 (d) On and after January 1, 2026, employer contributions and interest
9 as provided by K.S.A. 74-49,308, and amendments thereto, shall be used
10 by the system to offset the cost of the transfer of teacher members to the
11 Kansas public employees retirement system act of 2009. Members shall
12 have no right or obligation to such employer contributions and interest.
13 (e) On and after January 1, 2026, the board of trustees shall execute
14 such transfer and take all necessary steps to ensure that such transfer of
15 persons and assets authorized by this section does not affect the system's
16 applicable qualification requirements for governmental plans under the
17 federal internal revenue code.
18 (f) As used in this section, "teacher" means any professional
19 employee who is required to hold a certificate to teach in any school
20 district and any teacher or instructor in any technical college or community
21 college.
22 (g) This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the Kansas
23 public employees retirement system act of 2009, K.S.A. 74-49,201 et seq.,
24 and amendments thereto.
25 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 74-49,301 is hereby amended to read as follows: 74-
26 49,301. (a) The provisions of K.S.A. 74-49,301 through 74-49,318, and
27 amendments thereto, shall be known and may be cited as the Kansas
28 public employees retirement system act of 2015.
29 (b) Any employee who is first employed by a participating employer
30 on or after January 1, 2015, shall be a member of the system under the
31 provisions of this act on the first day of employment of such employee
32 with such participating employer.
33 (c) (1) Any non-vested nonvested employee other than an elected
34 official of a participating employer who has been employed in a covered
35 position as defined in K.S.A. 74-49,202, and amendments thereto, other
36 than with a school employer, shall remain a member of the Kansas public
37 employees retirement system as provided pursuant to K.S.A. 74-4901 et
38 seq., and amendments thereto, on and after July 1, 2009, if the member:
39 (A) Does not leave covered employment with a participating employer for
40 a period of time exceeding 30 consecutive days; (B) does not withdraw
41 such member's annuity savings account as defined by K.S.A. 74-49,302,
42 and amendments thereto, forfeiting such member's membership in the
43 interim; and (C) returns to covered employment with a participating

