1 employer in a covered position within such 30-day time period.
2 (2) Any non-vested nonvested employee other than an elected official
3 of a participating employer who has been employed in a covered position
4 with a participating school employer, shall remain a member of the Kansas
5 public employees retirement system as provided pursuant to K.S.A. 74-
6 4901 et seq., and amendments thereto, if the member: (A) Was employed
7 in a covered position with a participating school employer for the duration
8 of the school year and immediately returns to covered employment with
9 another participating school employer at the beginning of the following
10 school year; and (B) does not withdraw such member's annuity savings
11 account as defined by K.S.A. 74-49,302, and amendments thereto,
12 forfeiting such member's membership in the interim.
13 (d) This act does not apply to:
14 (1) Members of the Kansas police and firemen's retirement system,
15 K.S.A. 74-4951 et seq., and amendments thereto,;
16 (2) the retirement system for judges, K.S.A. 20-2601 et seq., and
17 amendments thereto, and;
18 (3) security officers as provided in K.S.A. 74-4914a, and
19 amendments thereto; and
20 (4) teachers as defined in section 1, and amendments thereto, who
21 are:
22 (A) First employed by a participating school employer on or after
23 July 1, 2025; or
24 (B) transferred to the group of members governed by the provisions
25 of the Kansas public employees retirement system act of 2009, K.S.A. 74-
26 49,201 et seq., and amendments thereto, on January 1, 2026, pursuant to
27 section 1, and amendments thereto.
28 (e) A system member may not simultaneously be a member of the
29 pre-2015 plan and the plan established pursuant to this act. A period of
30 service may not be credited in more than one retirement plan within the
31 system.
32 (f) The board of trustees of the Kansas public employees retirement
33 system shall administer the provisions of this act in the same manner as the
34 board administers the provisions of K.S.A. 74-4901 et seq., and
35 amendments thereto, except as specifically provided in this act.
36 (g) Unless specifically provided in this act, the provisions of K.S.A.
37 74-4901 et seq., and amendments thereto, shall be applicable to this act. In
38 an event that a conflict exists between the provisions of this act and the
39 provisions of K.S.A. 74-4901 et seq., and amendments thereto, the
40 provisions of this act shall control, and to that end, no legal or contractual
41 rights shall inure to the benefit of members or participating employers
42 under this act with regard to the provisions of K.S.A. 74-4901 et seq., and
43 amendments thereto, when the provisions of this act control.

